premise_source_doc_sentence: Symptoms of nutritional anemia can include fatigue and lack of energy .
Symptoms include anemia , jaundice , splenomegaly , and fatigue .

Symptoms of hemolytic anemia are similar to other forms of anemia  (  fatigue and shortness of breath  )  , but in addition , the breakdown of red cells leads to jaundice and increases the risk of particular long-term complications , such as gallstones and pulmonary hypertension .
The National Cancer Institute considers `` immunohemolytic anemia '' , `` autoimmune hemolytic anemia '' , and `` immune complex hemolytic anemia '' to all be synonyms .
Although MeSH uses the term `` autoimmune hemolytic anemia '' , some sources prefer the term `` immunohemolytic anemia '' so drug reactions can be included in this category .
